{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:14:05.540928+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: b7f48297d45c03a601414545c00525212f3a6fe8)", "id": "lc_42ef9fc6-e86e-4ea2-a8e2-03f3a482017b"}, {"type": "text", "text": "name: Deploy to ECR\n\non:\n  push:\n    branches: [ master ]\n\njobs:\n  build:\n    name: Build Image\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n\n\n    steps:\n      - name: Check out code\n        uses: actions/checkout@v2\n\n      - name: Configure AWS credentials\n        uses: aws-actions/configure-aws-credentials@v1\n        with:\n          aws-access-key-id: ${{ secrets.AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID }}\n          aws-secret-access-key: ${{ secrets.AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY }}\n          aws-region: ${{ secrets.AWS_REGION }}\n\n      - name: Login to Amazon ECR\n        id: login-ecr\n        uses: aws-actions/amazon-ecr-login@v1\n\n      - name: Build, tag, and push image to Amazon ECR\n        env:\n          ECR_REGISTRY: ${{ steps.login-ecr.outputs.registry }}\n          ECR_REPOSITORY: lantron-ecr-b5b2b12\n          IMAGE_TAG: react-admin\n        run: |\n          docker build -t $ECR_REGISTRY/$ECR_REPOSITORY:$IMAGE_TAG .\n          docker push $ECR_REGISTRY/$ECR_REPOSITORY:$IMAGE_TAG", "id": "lc_5182190d-c721-482d-ab4e-38648b487463"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "a98ff486-71e8-407d-bfe1-02f74a6c9527", "tool_call_id": "call_24254c5b0d80429a8c3872c4", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-07T20:14:28.408512+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Here's a comprehensive summary of how to run, build, and preview this React admin app:\n\n---\n\n## How to Run / Build / Preview This React Admin App\n\n### Stack\n\n- **Vite** (build tool & dev server)\n- **React 18** with **TypeScript**\n- **MUI (Material UI)** for components\n- **Yarn** as the package manager\n\n---\n\n### `package.json` (complete contents per README instructions)\n\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"vite-react-ts-admin\",\n  \"author\": \"@houko\",\n  \"licence\": \"MIT\",\n  \"version\": \"1.0.0\",\n  \"private\": false,\n  \"homepage\": \"https://reactZone.github.io/vite-react-ts-admin\",\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"dev\": \"cross-env NODE_ENV=local vite --host\",\n    \"dev:stg\": \"cross-env NODE_ENV=stg vite\",\n    \"serve\": \"vite preview --host\",\n    \"build\": \"vite build --mode prod\",\n    \"build:stg\": \"cross-env vite build --mode test\",\n    \"build:prod\": \"cross-env vite build --mode production\",\n    \"deploy\": \"gh-pages -d dist\",\n    \"lint\": \"eslint --ext .jsx,.js,.ts,.tsx .\",\n    \"fix\": \"yarn lint --fix\"\n  },\n  \"browserslist\": {\n    \"production\": [\">0.2%\", \"not dead\", \"not op_mini all\"],\n    \"development\": [\"last 1 chrome version\", \"last 1 firefox version\", \"last 1 safari version\"]\n  },\n  \"dependencies\": { /* React 18, MUI 5, ApexCharts, Formik, Framer Motion, React Router v6, etc. */ },\n  \"devDependencies\": { /* Vite 4, TypeScript 4.9, ESLint, Prettier, commitlint, gh-pages, etc. */ }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 1. One-Time Setup\n\n```bash\nyarn install\n# Or, if using Taskfile:\ntask init\n```\n\nThe `task init` command also installs global tools (`conventional-changelog-cli`, `standard-version`, `commitizen`) and copies the local env file into place.\n\n### 2. Environment Files\n\nThe app uses **Vite environment files** stored in the `envs/` directory. `vite.config.ts` loads them dynamically based on `NODE_ENV`:\n\n| File | `NODE_ENV` | Target | API Host |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `envs/.env.local` | `local` | Local development | `https://mock.local.lantron.ltd` |\n| `envs/.env.stg` | `stg` | Staging | `https://mock.stg.lantron.ltd` |\n| `envs/.env.prod` | `prod` | Production | `https://mock.lantron.ltd` |\n\nAll environments use port **10086** for the dev server and output to `dist/`.\n\n### 3. Running Locally (Development)\n\n```bash\n# Default local dev server (uses envs/.env.local)\nyarn dev\n# → NODE_ENV=local, opens on http://localhost:10086 with HMR\n\n# Staging-targeted dev server (uses envs/.env.stg)\nyarn dev:stg\n```\n\nThe dev server binds to `0.0.0.0` (via `--host`) so it's accessible on your LAN. Hot Module Replacement (HMR) is configured over WebSocket on the same port.\n\n### 4. Building for Different Environments\n\n| Command | What it does |\n|---|---|\n| `yarn build` | Builds with Vite `--mode prod` (loads `envs/.env.prod`) |\n| `yarn build:stg` | Builds for staging (`--mode test`, loads `envs/.env.stg`) |\n| `yarn build:prod` | Builds for production (`--mode production`, loads `envs/.env.prod`) |\n\nAll build commands output to the `dist/` directory.\n\n### 5. Previewing a Production Build Locally\n\n```bash\nyarn serve\n# → Runs `vite preview --host`, serves the dist/ folder on the configured port\n```\n\n### 6. Deploying\n\n#### GitHub Pages\n```bash\nyarn deploy\n# → Uses gh-pages to push dist/ to the GitHub Pages branch\n```\n\n#### Netlify\nA `netlify.toml` is present with a simple SPA catch-all redirect rule (`/* → /index.html`, status 200).\n\n#### Docker (Production Container)\n```bash\ndocker build -t react-admin .\ndocker run -p 80:80 react-admin\n```\nThe **Dockerfile** uses a multi-stage build:\n1. **Stage 1 (builder):** `node:lts-alpine` → runs `yarn` and `yarn build` to produce `dist/`.\n2. **Stage 2 (runtime):** `nginx:alpine` → copies `dist/` and a custom `nginx.conf` into the container, serving on port **80**.\n\nThe included `nginx.conf` enables gzip, listens on port 80, and rewrites all routes to `index.html` for proper SPA routing (including an `/admin` sub-path).\n\n#### AWS ECR (CI/CD)\nThe GitHub Actions workflow (`.github/workflows/push-image.yml`) automatically builds the Docker image and pushes it to **Amazon ECR** on pushes to the `master` branch.\n\n---\n\n### Quick-Reference Cheat Sheet\n\n| Task | Command |\n|---|---|\n| Install dependencies | `yarn install` or `task init` |\n| Local dev server | `yarn dev` (port 10086) |\n| Staging dev server | `yarn dev:stg` |\n| Production build | `yarn build:prod` |\n| Staging build | `yarn build:stg` |\n| Preview built output | `yarn serve` |\n| Lint | `yarn lint` |\n| Auto-fix lint issues | `yarn fix` |\n| Deploy to GitHub Pages | `yarn deploy` |\n| Docker build & run | `docker build -t react-admin . && docker run -p 80:80 react-admin` |", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 1391, "prompt_tokens": 9214, "total_tokens": 10605, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 19, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 8832, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0014081352, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.0001979652, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00121017}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780863245-EcVQRhiee3QgS8LBOhXj", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea3b8-9ce5-79c2-ad47-4f510a47e5f6-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 9214, "output_tokens": 1391, "total_tokens": 10605, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 8832}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 19}}}}]}}}
